{"cursor":"2117","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\n\n\n'Multi-tendency' when used in regard to a political organization, especially a\nleft-wing or anarchist one, means that the organization recognizes or at least\ntolerates members who are affiliated with or identify with a variety of\nideologies within the broad stance of the organization. It often distinguishes\nsuch organizations from those that adhere to a party line or a stringent credo.\n","linknr":127,"url":"Multi-tendency","recorded":1362675117,"links":21,"instances":["united_states","politics","united_states"],"pdf":[],"categories":["Anarchist theory","Socialism","Political party factions"],"headings":["Origin","See also","References"],"image":["//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/9/99/Question_book-new.svg/50px-Question_book-new.svg.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/12/Megaphon.png/25px-Megaphon.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/7a/Anarchy-symbol.svg/20px-Anarchy-symbol.svg.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/5b/Society.svg/45px-Society.svg.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/vector/images/search-ltr.png?303-4","//bits.wikimedia.org/images/wikimedia-button.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/poweredby_mediawiki_88x31.png"],"tags":[["party_line","politics"],["workers_party","united_states"],["socialist_workers_party","united_states"],["workers_party","united_states"]],"members":["socialist_workers_party","party_line","workers_party"],"related":["Left-wing","Anarchist","Ideology","Party_line_(politics)","Credo","Philip_Selznick","University_of_California,_Berkeley","Workers_Party_(United_States)","Trotskyists","James_Cannon","Socialist_Workers_Party_(United_States)","Max_Schachtman","Democratic_centralism","Independent_Socialist_League","Socialist_Party_of_America","Workers_Party_(United_States)","Party_platform","Manifesto"]}